<Paragraph>
The Taskbar control is used for grouping multiple items in desired layout with headers. This sample demonstrates the essential Taskbar control capabilities.</Paragraph>


<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>The visual styles denote  built-in themes, including metro, office themes, visual studio, etc</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Taskbar supports both the left-to-right and right-to-left layouts</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Orientation denotes vertical orientation of the taskbar elements and horizontal orientation positionings</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Customizes the expander icon for the delay in animation</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Provides options for displaying or hiding headers for every item</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Allows all the task bar items to either extend or collapse</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List> 
